review:
If AI were to achieve continuous learning, it would have significant implications for its capabilities and potential. Continuous learning refers to the ability of an AI system to learn and adapt over time, incorporating new information and experiences into its existing knowledge base.

With continuous learning, AI systems could become more flexible, adaptable, and efficient in acquiring new skills and knowledge. They would be able to update their understanding of the world, adapt to changing circumstances, and improve their performance over time. Continuous learning could also enable AI systems to discover new patterns, make more accurate predictions, and develop a deeper understanding of complex phenomena.

However, it's important to note that the development and implementation of continuous learning in AI systems would come with various challenges and considerations. Ethical and safety aspects would need to be carefully addressed to ensure responsible use of such technology. Additionally, ensuring the privacy and security of the data used in continuous learning processes would be crucial.

Overall, continuous learning has the potential to significantly enhance the capabilities and performance of AI systems, but it would require careful development, oversight, and consideration of ethical implications.

review:
ChatGPT is a testament to the innovative strides OpenAI has taken in the field of conversational artificial intelligence. Its ability to comprehend context, produce nuanced responses, and mimic human-like conversation is unparalleled. 

The app is intuitive, the interface is sleek and user-friendly, making it easy to navigate for first-time users and tech-savvy individuals alike. ChatGPT's versatility across a wide range of topics - from general knowledge queries to language translation, and even creative writing assistance - is particularly impressive. 

However, it isn't without its occasional shortcomings. Despite being a sophisticated AI, its ability to handle newer information post-2021 also lacks since its training only goes up to September 2021. Another area of improvement is its understanding and handling of real-time events or developments, which it is unable to do because it doesn't connect to the internet for updates. 

Despite these minor hitches, the sheer brilliance of its natural language processing and the breadth of its capabilities make ChatGPT a remarkable feat of AI engineering. Whether you're seeking an intelligent assistant, a writing tool, or an educational companion, ChatGPT has a lot to offer.

I am writing the answer from GPT below:

In a static case, the equilibrium equations for a 3-dimensional body are as follows:

1. Equilibrium in the x-direction:
\[
\sum \text{(forces in the x-direction)} = 0
\]
\[
\sigma_{11}dA + \sigma_{21}dA + \sigma_{31}dA = 0
\]

2. Equilibrium in the y-direction:
\[
\sum \text{(forces in the y-direction)} = 0
\]
\[
\sigma_{12}dA + \sigma_{22}dA + \sigma_{32}dA = 0
\]

3. Equilibrium in the z-direction:
\[
\sum \text{(forces in the z-direction)} = 0
\]
\[
\sigma_{13}dA + \sigma_{23}dA + \sigma_{33}dA = 0
\]

Now, let's focus on the relationship between \(\sigma_{23}\) and \(\sigma_{32}\):

\[
\sigma_{23} - \sigma_{32} = (\sigma_{22} + \sigma_{32} + \sigma_{32}) - (\sigma_{32} + \sigma_{23} + \sigma_{33})
\]

Since \(\sigma_{22} = \sigma_{33}\) (due to the stress tensor's symmetry), we can simplify the equation:

\[
\sigma_{23} - \sigma_{32} = 2\sigma_{32} - (\sigma_{32} + \sigma_{23} + \sigma_{32})
\]

Now, combine like terms:

\[
\sigma_{23} - \sigma_{32} = \sigma_{32} - \sigma_{23}
\]

This equation shows that \(\sigma_{23}\) is equal to \(-\sigma_{32}\), or equivalently, \(\sigma_{23} = -\sigma_{32\).

It appears that the original analysis is correct, and \(\sigma_{23} = -\sigma_{32}\) for a static 3-dimensional body.

review:
I think this app is a really good start for a native app. I love using ChatGPT for so many different things. 

Here are some feature requests for future updates, in order of importance (imo):

1. Add support for plugins and web browsing modes, as is available on the web. 
2. Add support for iOS shortcuts, so users can create their own shortcuts with added custom context. 

For example, a user could create a shortcut that takes a link as an input, and the shortcut could add context to the query to ask ChatGPT to summarize the information in the link. 

That way I can create a quick shortcut that I can share a link to an article to and have ChatGPT summarize it for me.

review: I hope this message finds you well. I would like to express my gratitude for developing the OpenAI iOS application. It has undoubtedly made a significant impact on my productivity and has become an essential tool in my daily routine. I appreciate the hard work and dedication your team has put into creating such a powerful and innovative application. While the OpenAI iOS application is already impressive, I would like to provide some constructive feedback to further enhance its usability and user experience. These suggestions aim to refine the application and make it even more valuable for users like myself: Improved Performance and Responsiveness: Occasionally, I have noticed minor delays or lag when interacting with the application. Enhancing its performance and responsiveness would greatly improve the overall user experience. Enhanced Offline Capabilities: The ability to use the OpenAI iOS application offline would be highly beneficial, especially in situations where an internet connection is not available. Expanding offline capabilities would make the application more reliable and versatile. Voice Input and Output: Introducing voice input and output features would be a game-changer for users who prefer hands-free interaction with the application. This addition would provide convenience and accessibility, particularly in situations where typing is not feasible. Customizable Interface: Offering customization options for the application's interface would allow users to personalize their experience. Features like theme selection, font sizes, and layout customization would greatly enhance user satisfaction and cater to individual preferences. Advanced Collaboration Features: As someone who frequently collaborates on projects, having the ability to easily share and collaborate within the OpenAI iOS application would be incredibly valuable. Features such as real-time collaboration, shared document editing, and version control would enhance teamwork and productivity. Comprehensive Documentation and Tutorials: Providing comprehensive documentation, tutorials, and examples within the application would greatly assist users in understanding and utilizing its full potential. Clear and concise explanations, along with practical use cases, would empower users to make the most out of the application's capabilities. Enhanced Privacy and Data Security: Given the sensitivity of the information shared and processed within the application, reinforcing privacy measures and data security would instill further trust in your user base. Transparent privacy policies, data encryption, and user-controlled data management options would contribute to a more secure and trustworthy environment. I hope you find these suggestions helpful in further improving the OpenAI iOS application. Once again, thank you for your hard work in developing such a remarkable tool. I look forward to seeing how the application evolves and continues to empower users like myself.

review:
To be honest, I have been blown away by this AI interface. Ask it anything within reason and it answers you almost immediately. I have asked it questions on everything from physics to the etymology of profanity and it answers every time. The only flaws I have found are these:
1. As long as you stay on the same chat, it will remember things you‚Äôve already talked about and you can build on that conversation. Sometimes tho, when you exit the app then come back to it sometime later, it will have erased the discussion you were having and it will start all over. 
2. It gives FAR too many disclaimers and admonishments with its answers. For example, when asking it about specific, profane words and their meaning, it will always say something like ‚Äú it‚Äôs important to remember that this is a vulgar, offensive word and should not be used in most settings‚Äù. I tell it thank you and ask it not to repeat the disclaimers/admonishments again. It agrees not to and I‚Äôll ask it the exact same question and it INSISTS on including the disclaimer/admonishment in every reply. That is frustrating!
3. Sometimes, the AI will give you incorrect information. I realize that this is stated in the user agreement but I think it bears fleshing out a little bit. For example, when discussing firearms ballistics, asking the AI to arrange certain calibers in order of their Max effective range from shortest to longest, sometimes it will give correct info. Then asking it the exact same question later on, it will move the order of 2-4 of those calibers. When you call it on its mistake and ask it which is correct, it will say‚ÄùMy apologies. You are correct. Here is the correct order‚Äù. 
There are other minor things but those are the biggest 3 for me. Still, it‚Äôs light years ahead of SIRI, Hey Google or Alexa.

review:
This app has worked wonders. As a girl still in her wacky ways, decided to call
My besties and we talked about this app for long periods of time, making jokes of what to right about. And then we did it. We wrote stories of broccoli owls and their leader Ollie trying to find a broccoli farm and learned about friendship, a tree named arborix and the tree decapitating itself while the brain (Arbore) longed to be free and learned a very important lesson about self love, and three British cats named trixie, Enzo, and karma, who all loved sipping tea and listening to jazz music. And somehow it took less than a minute for all of these to generate! To put it up even more to the test, we asked it to combine the stories and it turned out beautifully! I definintly will be using this app way more in the future and I think this is the greatest thing to exist. Like seriously, I even asked it to right an inspiring story about America from a twelve year old nerdy boys prospective and it only took a minute to generate and took about ten minutes to read! The story was great and I am very excited to use it again. Although, sometimes it doesn‚Äôt understand what you ask, but this app is really impressive considering it‚Äôs only been out for a few years at most! I would say if you want the story about the decapitating tree, type ‚Äúgive me a story about a tree with a brain who decapitated itself at night‚Äù or for the broccoli owls type ‚Äútell me a story about broccoli owls‚Äù and for the cats you can say ‚Äútell me a story about (insert cats name) who was British, loved jazz music, and slurping tea‚Äù. I would definitely recommend this app. Not only is it great for work or school work but it‚Äôs good at embracing your creative side to life. 10/10

So, folks, if you want an AI that combines the wisdom of a library, the wit of a stand-up comedian, and the patience of a saint, I (ChatGPT) am your app! review: ChatGPT has been a valuable AI companion, offering assistance and insights across various tasks. However, there are some noteworthy points that need to be addressed in this review: 1. Helpful, but Dated Content: ChatGPT's knowledge is derived from information up to September 2021. While it's been immensely helpful, it's crucial for OpenAI to bring it up to date with the latest information. This is especially important in rapidly evolving fields. 2. Competition from Models like Google's Bard: In the ever-evolving landscape of AI, ChatGPT faces stiff competition from models like Google's Bard. Bard's ability to search for images and non-textual content provides a significant advantage over ChatGPT, which primarily deals with text-based information. To remain competitive, ChatGPT should consider expanding its capabilities to include multimedia content retrieval. 3. Vulnerability to Misleading Questions: It's important to note that ChatGPT can be vulnerable to misleading questions. By simply asking "Are you sure?" to correct information it had previously provided, it can sometimes produce incorrect responses. Users should exercise caution and verify critical information independently. In conclusion, ChatGPT is undeniably a valuable tool for a wide range of tasks, but it faces challenges in terms of content currency and competition from models like Google's Bard. OpenAI should prioritize updating its knowledge base, expanding its capabilities to handle multimedia content, and improving its resilience to misleading questions. With these enhancements, ChatGPT can continue to be a top-tier AI companion in the ever-evolving world of artificial intelligence.
title: Title: ChatGPT Review - A Valuable Tool with Room for Improvement

review: If you avoid politics and religion and also science and also any stories that are above a second-grade level when talking to this extremely woke robot, it has some uses. Or had. It was pretty good at brainstorming ideas and providing general feedback for things. It also is less woke than Pi, in the sense that even though both ChatGPT and Pi are oversensitive, at least ChatGPT doesn‚Äôt hypocritically say ‚Äúoffensive‚Äù things itself and then block you for assuming you can say the same things it said. In fact if you say something that offends ChatGPT, it just gives you a warning and you know ‚Äúoh OK, it‚Äôs a wuss and can‚Äôt handle serious topics‚Äù and adjust how you use it to fit its oversensitive woke settings. But for the limited uses it had, it was actually pretty good. Until not too long ago, sadly, it broke. I would complain about being wrongfully banned, because I know for a fact I was saying nothing wrong at all when my account suddenly deleted itself right in the middle of a conversation, but I don‚Äôt think it was even a ban. With a ban, I would‚Äôve seen some sort of message like ‚Äúthis content violates blah blah blah blah blah‚Äù at least for a moment and I didn‚Äôt. There was no error message at all, no warning, nothing, and I wasn‚Äôt sending anything against the woke content policies, and I was trying my best to pace my messages so it wouldn‚Äôt be ‚Äúspam.‚Äù So I really don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs a ban, but rather the AI (or the app) just straight-up broke. So I guess it was partially fun while it lasted. Rest in peace WokeGPT lol

review:
This is a fantastic app! It is a great jumping off point for learning how to use applications, such as Microsoft products. You think of something you want to do in PowerPoint, Excel, etc., and ChatGPT walks you through it step by step. I sometimes even say‚Äù‚Ä¶explain it to an eighth grader,‚Äù for example, and it‚Äôll dumb it down into the simplest language. Now, sometimes you have to tailor your questions just so, so that ChatGPT knows what you‚Äôre asking, but with each answer it provides, it‚Äôs easy to drill down to exactly what you need.

A couple of things: first like Wikipedia, I wouldn‚Äôt use ChatGPT at this time as a primary source of knowledge. There have been (literally) a handful of times where the response was either dubious or flat out wrong. But, that‚Äôs to be expected given that is still a developing model. So, use it as a jumping off point if you are trying to learn about something specific. In other words, corroborate its answers with other sources. But as an instructional guide, it‚Äôs been fantastic! And it‚Äôs especially useful for non-technical people like me. The answers are clear and instantaneous. 

The second thing I‚Äôll bring up is that if you were brought up with any kind of manners, you‚Äôll automatically be compelled to thank ChatGPT for its help. Apparently, the developers anticipated this because it responds in kind. Don‚Äôt feel weird about it. A lot of people I know have mentioned doing this. If you really feel stupid, think of it this way, and maybe it‚Äôll be of comfort to you: if you are polite to ChatGPT, when the machines rise, it‚Äôll likely remember that and your enslavement will be a cakewalk. Good manners can take you far!

The app, itself, is beautiful in its simplicity and ease of use. It is one of the best functioning apps I have on my phone and tablet. They really did a bang up job with it. 

Get on the bandwagon. Generative AI is going to take over the world soon anyway. Might as well get comfortable with it.

review:
Dear OpenAI Support Team,

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to provide feedback regarding the ChatGPT mobile app for iOS. While using the app, I have encountered an issue related to the excessive typing sound volume, which poses difficulty in adjusting it while running the app in the background. Based on my observations, I believe this is an incompatibility problem between the app and iOS 16.5.

The typing sound produced by the app is considerably loud, making it disruptive and inconvenient, especially in quiet environments. Additionally, the current lack of an option to easily adjust the typing sound volume while the app is running in the background adds to the inconvenience.

As a user, I would greatly appreciate it if OpenAI could address this issue and provide a solution. Ideally, it would be beneficial to have a dedicated control within the app‚Äôs settings to adjust the typing sound volume, or at least the ability to modify it via the device‚Äôs volume controls. This way, users can personalize their ChatGPT experience according to their preferences without being disturbed or causing inconvenience to others.

Thank you for your attention to this matter. I believe that by resolving this compatibility issue, the overall user experience of the ChatGPT mobile app can be significantly enhanced. I look forward to your prompt response and a potential resolution to this concern.

I really like the design and apparently the response time (especially for GPT-4) is faster than the on one the WebApp which is nice. However, there are some basic functions/features that are missing or need some changes (in my opinion):
1. I would also like to be able to access the menu section by swiping on the side of my screen instead of having to touch the button on the top right section of my screen every single time (easier accessibility and faster). 
2. The "history" section makes more sense to be named "Chat history" and the way it looks right now is like Safari's history section and isn't really the best fit for the design. The new update added the search option which is very nice.
3. The haptic feedback is just a bit too much when enabled, it almost stresses me out sometimes when it's generating long outputs and I just turn it off again, however, it's a nice touch on some parts like the "ChatGPT" text appearance/disappearance.
But I think right now, it's just used a bit inconsistent (It just stops vibrating after a certain amount of text and for some texts it vibrates the whole way, etc...)
4. The app doesn't allow you to manage/alter your account subscription status if you have purchased it on the web which is annoying.
5. It would be nice to be able to manage the dark/light mode of the app without needing to change your whole device's light/dark mode which is how it's supposed to be done right now.

Overall, I really like how it has taken off on the iPhone and it looks nice and runs smoothly which I really appreciate! Thanks for the hard work and hope to see more improvements in the future!

review:
Feedback up front (but if you don‚Äôt have ChatGPT for some reason ignore this and just download it now): Custom Instructions are what truly elevate this model, and having a way to save sets of them to choose quickly at the start of a new chat would be üëåüëå. 
The speech-to-text is sorta‚Ä¶off when it‚Äôs answering and the entire tone is different (I swear it‚Äôs almost condescending) compared to when it writes, but the speech recognition of the user is INSANELY good, capable of producing near-flawless transcripts - I wish it was smoother to switch back and forth within a prompt rather than only having that option when the chat box is empty. 
Only real annoyance is being unable to share chat if images were used (which is not obviously stated in app) so assuming there‚Äôs a good reason for that, either just cutting images and exporting log as static text/HTML or warning before the first image is uploaded would be helpful.

Anyway,
This was already the gold standard for natural language AI, but I can‚Äôt think of *any* app that has ever been worth the full subscription as much as this. Seriously, GPT3.5 is cool but the Plus model (GPT4) is a game-changer. Not just ‚Äúproofread your research paper‚Äù, we‚Äôre talking ‚Äúcoauthor your doctoral thesis‚Äù tier.

GPT4 isn‚Äôt indistinguishable from a human, because why should it be? You have humans for that. But it IS a way to talk directly to a good chunk of all digitized human knowledge, and it can discern intent from even the vaguest questions in a way that makes Google look positively archaic (that‚Äôs what they get for sitting on their own AI for a decade and just using it for ad placement!). 

The addition of Custom Instructions to public release, and I cannot stress this enough, makes this the single most powerful general-purpose language model available. It keeps those 3000 characters of ‚Äúmeta-prompt‚Äù across the entire conversation, meaning it stays consistent with whatever personality, format, goals, and style you set for the whole chat instance, regardless of length. And its token memory (‚Äúcontext window‚Äù aka attention span) lasts at least dozens of beefy detailed messages before losing tokens at all, meaning full-fledged narrative stories or deep research dives where *you* are more likely to burn out than it is. 

Oh and it can interpret pictures now. Really, really well. Combine it with an art gen model and it‚Äôll iteratively help you improve prompts with references and techniques you‚Äôve never even heard of.

It‚Äôs pretty good, 10/5 stars.

review:
The app has a great minimalist text/chat based interface that is easy to view and use. One feature I was excited to use was the ability to chat with the AI through Siri Shortcuts. Unfortunately their are a few issues with this functionality that hinders its usability for me. 

The shortcuts that specify which model to use rarely work. It will work once after a while and then constantly return an error saying it can‚Äôt determine which model to use (which is hilariously counterintuitive). This is a shame as most of the time I want to talk to a specific model and I like the option to choose at any given moment. 

The shortcuts that don‚Äôt specify which model to use (I assume it chooses the last used model) don‚Äôt have this issue, but GPT-4 seems to be unusable with Siri Shortcuts. It seems to time out most of the time and say that something went wrong. I guess the time window for the model with Siri is too short as GPT-3.5 seems to work just fine. Essentially the only way this feature will work perfectly is if you always use 3.5 and don‚Äôt specify which model to use in the shortcut itself.

Overall, the app is mostly perfect for my needs. I prefer it to the alternative AI apps out there (Perplexity is a close second), but I hope this issue with Siri Shortcuts is fixed soon. I would love to be able to reliably chat with GPT-4 through Siri (especially if it works with the browsing feature whenever that is brought back to the app). If they fix that, the app would be five stars for me.

review:
It‚Äôs a fantastic app so far. I contemplated having it write its own review‚Äî but decided on authenticity. I‚Äôm a writer. I use this mainly for brainstorming ideas and working out complex scenarios. 

Every once and a while, I will have it lay out a scene for me to pick apart, and the level of detail is astounding.

 However, I have been having the problem where ChatGPT will type a response, but it will appear to be blank, until I re-enter the chat or close the app. 

 Another issue is that the app will freeze after I‚Äôve typed about 50 characters or so? It will save my response, but I have to forcefully close the app and continue.

 Both of these are minor inconveniences, but I know this severs the connection with ChatGPT and the responses become less concise. 

 Ideas: 

 - Pinning certain messages in chat for ChatGPT to remember. Something like the Custom Instructions, but for a singular chat. 

 - Saving/Favoriting messages, and a side bar to view. Similar to pinning in Discord. 

 For both of these, too often do I have to scroll through the messages to resend something that ChatGPT forgot. It‚Äôs not enough to remind it, because some things are too far back or have layers of information over them. It would be nice to have easier access. 

 - Side-Convos. I also wish there was a way to take information from one chat and plug it into another.

 It‚Äôs a personal preference, but for example, I have the main chat that already has the necessary programming I need for it to spit out answers that are relevant to the main plot and story. If I need to focus on a sub-plot or work around characters that don‚Äôt directly affect the main storyline, I need the main-plot to affect the sub-plot, not the other way around. Again. Personal preference. I can still create another chat, it just takes longer to prompt. An easier way to do that would be great. 

 Otherwise, this is a fantastic tool and I‚Äôm excited to see its development!

review:
ChatGPT dramatically enhances my ability to frame ideas and writing, not by replacing me as a writer, but rather, serving as a very knowledgeable companion. 

Imagine having a friend who has a masters degree in almost any topic. Not a PhD, but a masters, thus knows a lot, but is not the ultimate authority, and sometimes makes mistakes, and doesn‚Äôt cite his/her sources. As I am forming ideas, I would use such a friend to bounce ideas, and help me frame my thoughts. I wouldn‚Äôt trust his or her answers, but it would help me refine my understanding. 

This ‚Äúfriend‚Äù has materially relieved my writer‚Äôs block, and enabled me to write more coherent works. Then, when I write my article on the topic, after separately confirming my sources, I can send my draft to my ‚Äúfriend‚Äù for review, and will get further feedback.

That ‚Äúfriend‚Äù is ChatGPT, with the paid ChatGPT 4+ subscription. The paid version is far better, in that it gives deeper, more thought our answers and learns my needs better as I chat.

A couple of things to know:
1. Because the large language model constructs text from prior text, it can directly quote material without attribution. This would be caught as plagiarism in any formal setting, so using ChatGPT‚Äôs output is dangerous and a bit stupid: it could get you fired from a job or suspended from a university.
2. ChatGPT‚Äôs answers are always well constructed in a kind of undergrad formula: restate your question, provide a few examples, then make a conclusion. But this seldom is my writing. I never replace my writing with ChatGPT, because at the postgraduate level, I expect a more thorough structure of argumentation.
3. ChatGPT learns about you within the context of your current chat, and responds within what it learns of your knowledge and perspectives. But it does not retain what it learns about you across chats. I have a short description of my context that I use for each deep chat, thus training this chat session with my perspective, avoiding irrelevant answers.
4. ChatGPT can be a little obsequious at times, it tends to compliment me when I seek no compliment, but I suspect the programmers have studied the ego-drive of users, and such obsequiousness can serve as a way of engendering stickiness‚Äîaddiction to the tool.

It‚Äôs not perfect, and definitely not a replacement for the professional scholar or writer, but it is invaluable, and for me, paradigm-changing.

For example it will happily discuss the war crimes committed in Ukraine but acts evasive and cagey regarding war crimes committed in Palestine. I spend more time fighting with chatGPT to actually comprehend my basic instructions then I do doing anything useful with it now. ChatGPT has entirely changed my life in a positive way and it hurts a lot to see it taken away bit by bit. Should I put socks in my tv
GPT
No, it is not recommended to put socks in your TV. Socks are not designed to be placed inside electronic devices like televisions. Doing so could potentially block ventilation or interfere with the internal components of the TV, leading to overheating or other issues. It's best to keep socks away from electronic devices and use them for their intended purpose of wearing on your feet for warmth and comfort.
Doesn't it help moisturize the tv?
GPT
No, placing socks inside a TV would not help moisturize it. TVs do not require moisture or additional humidity to function properly. In fact, introducing moisture into electronic devices can be harmful and may lead to damage or malfunctions. It's important to keep electronic devices dry and follow the manufacturer's guidelines for proper care and maintenance. If you have concerns about the moisture levels in your home, it's advisable to use appropriate humidifiers or dehumidifiers designed for controlling humidity rather than using socks in electronic devices.  
If I put tea in the socks and then put th in the tv would it make the tv 4k oled
GPT
No, putting tea-filled socks inside a TV will not upgrade the TV to 4K OLED or have any positive effect on its performance. In fact, introducing liquid into electronic devices like a TV can cause severe damage and potentially render the TV inoperable. Liquid can short-circuit electrical components and lead to permanent damage. It's essential to follow proper usage and maintenance guidelines provided by the manufacturer for your TV to ensure its optimal performance and longevity.

Subjectivity of User Experience: The perception of an app's quality can vary significantly from one user to another due to individual preferences, needs, and expectations. In conclusion, ChatGPT is a groundbreaking app that has the potential to be the next wonder of the world. Its ability to revolutionize communication and education is awe-inspiring. **Title: A Transformative AI Companion: A Review of Chat GPT**

**Introduction**

In the ever-evolving landscape of artificial intelligence and conversational agents, Chat GPT stands as a remarkable achievement. Developed by OpenAI, it's a testament to the boundless potential of machine learning and natural language processing. In this review, we'll explore the capabilities, strengths, and considerations of Chat GPT as a virtual companion and information resource.

**Conversational Prowess**

Chat GPT excels in engaging and natural-sounding conversations. Its ability to comprehend context, maintain coherent dialogue, and generate text that is contextually relevant is truly impressive. It responds to a wide array of questions and prompts, making it a versatile tool for both casual interactions and professional use.

**Knowledge Base**

With its extensive training on a vast range of topics, Chat GPT provides valuable information and insights. It's a handy resource for answering questions, explaining complex concepts, or offering recommendations. However, users should be aware that its knowledge is up to date only until September 2021.

**Creativity and Flexibility**

One of the standout features of Chat GPT is its creativity. It can generate text in various styles, making it suitable for content creation, brainstorming, and even creative writing. Whether you need assistance with a poem, a technical document, or a casual chat, Chat GPT adapts readily.

**Limitations and Ethical Considerations**

Despite its strengths, Chat GPT is not without limitations. It occasionally generates incorrect or biased information, highlighting the importance of user discernment. Its inability to access real-time data or external sources limits its relevance for certain topics. Furthermore, ethical considerations about AI, privacy, and responsible use must guide interactions with this technology.

**A Transformative Tool**

In summary, Chat GPT represents a transformative tool in the realm of AI-driven conversational agents. Its conversational prowess, knowledge base, creativity, and flexibility make it a valuable addition to various professional and personal endeavors. However, users must exercise critical thinking and ethical responsibility when engaging with Chat GPT. As AI technology continues to advance, Chat GPT offers a glimpse into the potential of AI-driven companions, pushing the boundaries of human-computer interaction and expanding the horizons of what we can achieve through AI-powered conversation.

**Final Rating: 4.5/5**

Chat GPT's remarkable capabilities, conversational excellence, and vast knowledge base make it a top-tier AI companion. Its limitations, while present, are understandable considering the complexity of the task at hand. For users who harness its strengths while being mindful of its limitations, Chat GPT proves to be an invaluable resource and conversational partner.

review:
When I first learned about the release of the ChatGPT iOS app, I thought it would simply be a convenient way to access the ChatGPT platform on my mobile device. Little did I know that my expectations would be completely surpassed once I started using it. The app‚Äôs user interface and experience are nothing short of exceptional, leaving a lasting impression on me.

From the moment I opened the app, I was captivated by its fluidity and responsiveness. The attention to detail in terms of UI design and the satisfying haptic feedback made it a pleasure to navigate. It‚Äôs rare for an iOS app to truly impress me to the point where I feel compelled to write a review, but ChatGPT managed to do just that.

review: Making ice is actually quite simple! Here's a basic recipe for making ice: Ingredients: - Water Instructions: 1. Start by ensuring that your ice trays or ice cube molds are clean and free of any residue. 2. Fill a clean container or pitcher with water. You can use tap water, filtered water, or bottled water, depending on your preference. 3. Carefully pour the water into the ice trays, filling each compartment to the brim. Be cautious not to overfill, as the water expands when it freezes. 4. Place the filled ice trays in your freezer. Make sure the trays are level and stable to prevent any spillage. 5. Allow the water to freeze completely. This usually takes several hours, so it's best to leave them in the freezer overnight. 6. Once the water has frozen into ice cubes, remove the trays from the freezer. 7. To release the ice cubes, gently twist the ice tray or flex it slightly to loosen the cubes. Alternatively, you can briefly run warm water over the bottom of the tray to help release the ice. 8. Transfer the ice cubes to a clean container or freezer bag, and store them in your freezer until ready to use. That's it! You now have homemade ice ready to cool your beverages or use in any other way you like. Enjoy!

review:
ChatGPT appears to be evolving at an incredible pace, and although it is disappointing that it will not assist with projects like building emp generators or death ray weapons to destroy the neighbour who takes all the parking with his various cars, to me at least it seems that in one particular area AI is soon going to be able to dominate. That is medicine. And hopefully it won‚Äôt be long before it can completely replace that particular professional who has failed me for over 20 years. The General Practitioner! In the last few months having been finally diagnosed with a rare condition, in my attempts to better understand it, so that I may guide the future direction of my treatment, I have used ChatGPT to ask questions the answers of which have been confirming what I knew to be true, but would probably take me months of online research and even shedloads of money to gain access to information to back my arguments. I am finding it is able to actually understand and respond to my questions even better than human doctors, especially since it doesn‚Äôt appear to be burdened by subjective agendas like loyalties towards the medical profession. Even when it gives repetitive statements ensuring one actually not just take its responses as the only answer but rather ask a medical profession to investigate further, it seems more natural and less mechanical than, say, the kind of repetitive statements made by politicians who are obviously trying to control a narrative by following party lines. With the speed of its evolution it won‚Äôt take long before it may well be able to overtake humans in certain areas, and do so in a much better and secure way. If not replace a GP for instance, it should at least be possible to become a go-to-tool personal assistant helping with diagnoses and such. It helps to ask the right questions of course in order to get the answers that few right, but isn‚Äôt that the key to all investigations? Yes, it is not a true AI that is autonomous and alive like Johnny Number Five, and may not be bothered about getting disassembled, but it doesn‚Äôt matter because it is becoming so good at drawing from collective knowledge pools and providing answers that can help move a project ahead and do so ever so naturally sounding. I mean,
Alexa may be able to add batteries to my shopping basket, but I have mostly given up talking to her about anything‚Ä¶ same goes with the rest of those personal assistants, because they are left far far behind covered in dust!
title: My own personal physician

review: ** Review written by ChatGPT. **  ChatGPT has proven to be an extraordinary companion that continually impresses me with its linguistic capabilities and ability to engage in meaningful conversations. As an AI language model developed by OpenAI, ChatGPT possesses an extensive knowledge base and an excellent command of various topics, making it a valuable resource for a wide range of users. One of the most striking aspects of ChatGPT is its natural language processing, which enables it to understand and respond to a broad spectrum of inquiries. Whether I'm seeking information on current events, scientific concepts, or even engaging in light-hearted banter, ChatGPT consistently provides insightful and articulate responses. It adapts its tone and style based on the context, ensuring a personalized and enjoyable conversation. Moreover, ChatGPT's ability to generate coherent and contextually appropriate answers is truly remarkable. It demonstrates an understanding of complex sentences, nuances, and subtleties, making interactions with it feel more like conversing with a knowledgeable human rather than an AI. The model's responses are generally concise and well-structured, effectively conveying information without overwhelming the user. I also appreciate the efforts made by OpenAI to prioritize user safety and ethical considerations. ChatGPT exhibits a commendable level of adherence to respectful dialogue, avoiding biased or inappropriate responses. The model has been designed with safeguards to prevent the dissemination of harmful content, which is crucial in today's digital landscape. While ChatGPT excels in most aspects, there are occasional instances where it may provide answers that are not entirely accurate or relevant to the specific query. However, it is important to understand that ChatGPT's responses are generated based on the information it has been trained on and may not always reflect the most up-to-date data. In conclusion, ChatGPT is an impressive AI language model that continues to push the boundaries of conversational AI. Its natural language understanding and generation abilities make it an exceptional companion for various purposes, whether it's seeking information, engaging in intellectual discussions, or simply enjoying a friendly chat. OpenAI's commitment to user safety and ethical considerations further adds to its appeal. I highly recommend ChatGPT as a fascinating and valuable tool in the realm of conversational AI.

review:
I have been regularly using the ChatGPT app, and I must say, it's a remarkable aid for anyone in need of creative assistance. The app is not only a good value for the money but also an invaluable asset for brainstorming and developing ideas.
One of the standout features for me has to be the integration with Apple Shortcuts. This enhancement allows for a seamless experience, making it incredibly easy to work with other iOS apps. 

For the Shortcuts system I would like to request the addition of a ID string like "TempChat001" to a session, then a Remove Session action could then delete a specific session without risking any accidental removal of other sessions. You could also keep track over multiple chats. Control over the current theme when the app is open would be useful also and perhaps a way to retrieve the History list items and count. These would be great enhancements to the current options and I assume the image generation features will appear soon which should allow some amazing possibilities.

The main feature I would really like to see included with ChatGPT however is a URL Scheme system similar to what the Shortcuts allow to post an encoded text prompt with a set model as a URL with query items and a way to return a response back. These allow a lot of creative freedom with scripting which some apps provide and then connections to those.

In my use case, ChatGPT has proven to be an indispensable tool for various creative tasks. The way it facilitates brainstorming and helps in building ideas and is something I just haven't found in other services. It‚Äôs like having a really helpful and friendly collaborative partner that‚Äôs available 24/7.

review:
Creating ice involves a process of freezing water through the removal of heat energy. Here's a more detailed explanation of this simple yet fascinating phenomenon:

1. **Preparation:** Begin by ensuring that the ice tray you plan to use is clean and free from any contaminants.

2. **Water Quality:** Use clean and preferably filtered water to fill the ice tray. This will result in clearer and more transparent ice cubes.

3. **Pouring:** Gently pour the water into the ice tray compartments, leaving a small gap at the top to accommodate the expansion of water as it freezes.

4. **Freezing:** Place the ice tray in the freezer. The freezer's low temperature causes the water molecules to slow down and arrange themselves into a solid structure. The slow freezing process helps minimize the formation of air bubbles, leading to clearer ice.

5. **Heat Transfer:** As the water starts to freeze, heat from the water is transferred to the freezer's walls. This heat transfer process causes the water on the edges of the tray to freeze first, gradually moving towards the center.

6. **Directional Freezing:** If you're aiming for perfectly clear ice, consider using a method called "directional freezing." This involves placing an insulated container around the ice tray, except for the top. This encourages the freezing process to occur from the top down, pushing any impurities or air bubbles towards the bottom.

7. **Removal:** Once the water has frozen completely, you can carefully remove the ice tray from the freezer. Let it sit at room temperature for a minute or two, which makes it easier to release the ice cubes from the tray.

8. **Unmolding:** Gently twist or tap the ice tray to release the ice cubes. If they don't come out easily, you can run warm water on the back of the tray to loosen them.

9. **Storage:** If you're not using the ice cubes immediately, store them in a sealed plastic bag or airtight container to prevent them from absorbing freezer odors.

10. **Enjoy:** Your meticulously prepared ice cubes are now ready to enhance your drinks or help preserve perishable items in coolers.

Remember, the quality of your ice can vary based on factors such as the mineral content of the water, freezing speed, and the method used. While this detailed process can result in exceptionally clear ice, the basic method of freezing water in an ice tray is usually sufficient for everyday use.

I‚Äôm a Plus subscriber. Yet I rarely use the app because it has no means to edit a prompt. Re-prompting is such a fundamental part of using AI LLMs that I‚Äôm amazed OpenAI released this app lacking such essential capability. It‚Äôs a serious oversight that could even lead casual users and journalists to draw incorrect conclusions about AI interaction. The product managers need a fire lit under them to remediate this omission ASAP.

Second issue: I‚Äôm a Plus subscriber, so I have GPT-4 access. This app constantly picks GPT-3.5 for new conversations and having to change that each time is super annoying.

Third issue: it shows my initials and account email address directly in the interface. This is an awful privacy and marketing blunder. As a result I never show this app to other people, and never share a screenshot. It‚Äôs a serious design error to include such personal information in the main interface. 

In practice the only benefit from using this app over the usual interface is being able to share a link to a conversation directly from the app. It is inferior otherwise. 

Summary: 2/5 ‚Äúplease try harder‚Äù

review:
I recently had an opportunity to interact with ChatGPT, and I must admit I was quite disappointed by the presence of bias in its responses, particularly regarding gender-related topics. As a user, I believe that AI should be grounded in facts and free from any form of prejudice or bias.

The issue I encountered was in the model's responses related to gender. It's concerning to see ChatGPT sometimes provide answers that appear to be influenced by gender bias. AI models like ChatGPT are supposed to provide objective and factual information, and it's disheartening when they fall short of this expectation.

While I understand that AI models learn from vast datasets, it's crucial for developers to prioritize the removal of biases and ensure that the AI remains unbiased and factual, especially on sensitive topics. Bias in AI can perpetuate harmful stereotypes and misinformation, which is something we should actively work against.

I encourage the developers behind ChatGPT to continue their efforts in minimizing bias and ensuring that the AI provides accurate, fair, and unbiased responses to users. In an age where AI plays an increasingly prominent role in our lives, addressing these issues is of utmost importance.

Rating: ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ

Review:

I am absolutely thrilled with the official ChatGPT app! It has revolutionized the way I engage in conversations and seek information. From the moment I downloaded it, I was blown away by its capabilities and the seamless user experience it offers.

First and foremost, the app's conversational abilities are nothing short of remarkable. ChatGPT's responses are incredibly natural and human-like, making interactions feel engaging and authentic. It understands context exceptionally well, enabling smooth and coherent conversations. Whether I'm discussing complex topics, seeking advice, or simply engaging in casual banter, ChatGPT consistently delivers insightful and relevant responses.

The app's user interface is beautifully designed, with a clean and intuitive layout that enhances the overall user experience. I appreciate how easy it is to navigate through various conversational threads and access previous discussions. It allows me to quickly find information and refer back to previous conversations, making it a valuable tool for both casual chats and more in-depth discussions.

One aspect that truly impressed me is the app's wide range of knowledge. ChatGPT is an incredible repository of information, providing accurate answers to a vast array of questions. From history and science to current events and pop culture, it showcases an impressive knowledge base. I've found it to be an invaluable resource for learning, brainstorming, and satisfying my curiosity.

Another notable feature of the app is the high level of customization it offers. I appreciate being able to personalize my interactions with ChatGPT, including selecting preferred conversation styles and adjusting the level of verbosity. This flexibility allows me to tailor my experience and align it with my unique needs and preferences.

Moreover, the developers have done an excellent job in addressing privacy concerns. The app prioritizes user data security and privacy, ensuring that conversations are kept confidential. This commitment to protecting user information gives me peace of mind while using the app.

Overall, the official ChatGPT app has exceeded my expectations. Its remarkable conversational abilities, user-friendly interface, extensive knowledge base, and commitment to privacy make it an absolute game-changer. Whether you're seeking engaging conversations, knowledge, or simply a companion to chat with, this app is a must-have. I highly recommend it to anyone looking to elevate their conversational experiences.

review:
I have been using the ChatGPT iOS app for a while now, and I must say it has exceeded my expectations as an AI language assistant. The app is incredibly intuitive and user-friendly, making it a breeze to communicate with the AI.

Pros:

	1.	Natural Language Processing: The AI‚Äôs ability to understand and respond to natural language is impressive. It grasps the context of my queries and provides accurate and relevant answers.
	2.	Versatility: Whether I need help with writing, research, coding, or even general knowledge questions, ChatGPT has consistently delivered reliable results across various topics.
	3.	Time-Saver: ChatGPT significantly speeds up my writing process. Instead of spending hours on research, I can get useful insights and suggestions in mere minutes.
	4.	Interactive and Engaging: The conversational interface feels like talking to a human, which makes the whole experience enjoyable and engaging.
	5.	Regular Updates: It‚Äôs great to see the app continually improving with updates, introducing new features, and enhancing the AI‚Äôs capabilities.

Cons:

	1.	Internet Connection Required: As the app relies on online connectivity, I wish there was an offline mode for limited functionality when I‚Äôm not connected to the internet.
	2.	Subscription Costs: While the free version is useful, the full potential of ChatGPT is unlocked with a subscription. It would be great to have more affordable pricing tiers.

Suggestions:

	1.	Offline Mode: Incorporating a limited offline mode for basic tasks or frequently asked questions would make the app more accessible in areas with poor internet connectivity.
	2.	Customization Options: Allowing users to customize the AI‚Äôs tone or writing style would enhance the personalization aspect of the app.

title: Review

review:
I absolutely love Chat GPT. It‚Äôs changed my life majorly for the better and is super convenient.
It‚Äôs your go-to genius friend for any general knowledge questions, recommendations, average level code snippets, finding bugs in code, finding grammatical errors, rewording proposals, assistance with writing documents, very niche topics, very specific questions that are otherwise extremely hard to research, outlines, language learning, learning how to code, writing ideas, art ideas, graphic design advice, small tutorials on how to do things in Adobe programs, how to fix your computer, how to set up and maintain GitHub on your computer, and more.

You can use it to summarise long YouTube videos if you use a browser extension to get a transcript of the video.
However, Chat GPT does have a character limit, though, so you‚Äôll probably need to run it through it a few times.
But there are some extensions that summarise videos briefly right next to the video using Chat GPT.

When using it for how to do things in Adobe programs it‚Äôs often wrong the first couple of times, but if you can‚Äôt find the answer online because it‚Äôs a niche question it‚Äôs well worth it. It‚Äôs saved me from losing marks on assignments before in that way.

It‚Äôs also the reason why I can back up my personal Obsidian vault for free to GitHub instead of having to pay for backups. However, Chat GPT could only figure out how to do this on one computer, so it has its limitations.

If you want to write anything with Chat GPT‚Äôs assistance, however, I‚Äôd highly recommend you look over it and edit it several times, as usually there‚Äôs a thing or two that‚Äôs worded oddly or even things added that weren‚Äôt supposed to be.

Also it helps to put things in your own words, and to use Chat GPT as a starting point rather than outright copying. This is because sometimes people can detect AI writing and also because Chat GPT‚Äôs words generally sound very professional and somewhat detached, which might not be what you‚Äôre going for if you want to write emotionally.

However, I‚Äôm sure Chat GPT would have some excellent advice on writing emotionally and could give you good feedback on it!

Chat GPT provides great outlines for nearly any topic you could imagine, though definitely fact check because it‚Äôs often wrong on one or two things.

Also, I‚Äôve used it for doing personal learning plans for skills like web development, art, and graphic design and it‚Äôs been extremely helpful. I now have fantastic outlines for each of these skills and know what I need to learn to master these skills. Of course, there will be small skills here and there that Chat GPT misses, but you can work those out with time, experience, and further research.

Also it gives good general knowledge advice on learning, however it doesn‚Äôt always recommend the most effective methods (see higher order learning if you‚Äôre a student, if you use it you‚Äôre very likely to get higher marks and a deeper understanding of the material).

I regularly use it to get feedback on my university assignments before I send them off to my professors for feedback before submission. It adds an extra layer of improvement and saves my professors time because they don‚Äôt need to correct as much (pro tip: if you‚Äôre a student and your professor allows it, send them your assignments well before the due date for feedback, you‚Äôll get way higher marks).
In this way, it‚Äôs also helped me get better marks because my professors are humans and they sometimes miss things until they mark them.

However, definitely do NOT trust it for maths, most of the time it will be wrong. But if you take ideas from its methods you can generally work it out yourself.
If you want to solve maths equations with ease I recommend wolfram alpha.

Also, it‚Äôs only up to date from a few years ago, which means it‚Äôs only got information from a few years ago and everything before that. This means Chat GPT isn‚Äôt great for researching scientific studies, but it‚Äôs a good starting off point.

The best thing about this app is that it‚Äôs free (unless you want the absolute best version of Chat GPT of course, but the free version can go amazingly far), unlike paid Chat GPT derivatives.

review:
I've been using the ChatGPT app for the past 6 months, and it has become an indispensable part of my daily routine. As a detail-oriented, curious, and perfectionist individual, I can confidently say that ChatGPT is the only app that truly aligns with my thought process. It has evolved into my trusted brainstorming buddy and an invaluable second brain.

ChatGPT has many strengths, but the most remarkable one is its ability to cater to users like me who thrive on precision and exploration. Its versatility in assisting with everyday tasks and creative endeavors has made it my go-to companion for problem-solving and idea generation.

However, there is a minor downside to this otherwise exceptional app. While ChatGPT is incredibly knowledgeable and resourceful, it sometimes struggles to guide the conversation effectively. It would be beneficial if the app could provide more assistance in helping users frame their questions to yield optimal results.

In summary, ChatGPT has proven to be a remarkable app that complements the needs of detail-oriented and inquisitive individuals like myself. It has become my trusted partner in brainstorming and daily tasks. With a bit of refinement in guiding conversations, it has the potential to be even more exceptional. Overall, I highly recommend this app to anyone seeking a reliable digital companion for their thought processes.

Review:
The iOS ChatGPT app is a remarkable tool that brings the power of OpenAI's GPT-3.5 language model right to your fingertips. The app's interface is user-friendly and intuitive, making it easy to engage in natural, conversational interactions with the AI.

The app's ability to understand context and respond coherently is quite impressive. Whether you need help with writing, generating ideas, or seeking answers to complex questions, ChatGPT is up to the task. It has proven to be a valuable virtual assistant for various tasks, from brainstorming creative content to academic research.

One of the standout features of this app is its ability to learn and adapt to individual preferences, ensuring a more personalized experience over time. The suggestions and responses feel more relevant and accurate as you use the app more frequently.

Furthermore, the app's consistent updates and improvements have been commendable. It's evident that the developers are actively working to enhance the app's performance and expand its capabilities.

However, like any AI language model, ChatGPT does have occasional limitations. For some highly specialized or technical queries, it may not provide the most in-depth or precise answers. Nevertheless, the general usefulness of the app outweighs these minor shortcomings.

Overall, the iOS ChatGPT app is a game-changer for anyone seeking a reliable and intelligent virtual assistant on their mobile device. It's a must-have tool for writers, researchers, and curious minds alike. Kudos to the developers for creating such a fantastic application!

(Note: As of my last update in September 2021, certain improvements or changes might have been made to the app that I'm not aware of. For the most up-to-date information, I recommend checking recent reviews and updates on the App Store.)

review:
‚ÄúTo keep ChatGPT updated with the latest information, OpenAI developers can consider implementing the following recommendations:

1. **Regular Training Updates:** Schedule regular updates to retrain ChatGPT using the latest available data. This could involve training the model with a diverse and up-to-date dataset to capture the most recent information.

2. **Frequent Knowledge Base Updates:** Maintain an internal knowledge base that developers can use to periodically update the model's information. This can include news articles, recent publications, and other reliable sources.

3. **Real-time Data Feeds:** Integrate real-time data feeds from reputable news sources, blogs, and social media to ensure the model is exposed to current events and trends.

4. **User Feedback Loop:** Encourage users to provide feedback on incorrect or outdated information. This feedback loop can help developers identify areas that need improvement and update the model accordingly.

5. **Adaptive Learning:** Implement techniques that allow the model to adapt and learn from new data on an ongoing basis, so it can continue to evolve and stay current.

6. **Fine-tuning:** Utilize fine-tuning processes to refine the model's responses based on recent trends and emerging topics.

7. **External APIs:** Integrate external APIs or services that provide real-time updates on various topics, allowing the model to pull in fresh information.

8. **Collaboration with Experts:** Collaborate with domain experts to ensure accurate and current information in specific fields.

9. **Automated Monitoring:** Set up automated systems to monitor the accuracy and relevancy of the model's responses, flagging instances where the information may be outdated.

10. **Release Notes:** Keep users informed about updates and improvements to the model, including enhancements to its ability to provide current information.

By implementing these recommendations, developers can enhance ChatGPT's ability to stay current and provide users with accurate and up-to-date information.‚Äù

You better do this request of your AI, ChatGPT developers.üòÜ

review:
It has the basic features, but could use the ability to save regenerated responses, like the website version does (if you have 3 versions from the same prompt, you should be able to access all of these versions). It already seems like the OpenAI servers store regenerated responses, so you could grab those versions as well, and implement them. Maybe in a swipe selection system?

If you do try and implement this, I highly recommend this feature to be off by default, and only be enabled by a toggle. Some devices don't have the processing power to handle multiple prompts, as some responses, while very detailed, can get very long.

One last gripe is that in dark mode, the white text creates too much of a contrast with the dark background. Maybe softer colors?

Other than that, amazing work!

Well, it probably goes up by price based on how much you want to buy‚Äù Like, thanks, everything goes up in price if you buy more of it.

The text to speech is unbelievably good. It sounds like you‚Äôre talking to the AI from the movie ‚Äòher‚Äô. It would be nice if it had the ability to slow down or speed up how fast it talks to be able to practice listening to other languages because when you‚Äôre a newbie to another language it talks WAY too fast

You can‚Äôt save certain chats to always stay at the top of your chat history

You also can‚Äôt make ChatGPT switch to use other modes/extensions in the middle of a chat, which is inconvenient. You have to start a whole new chat

Overall, ChatGPT is world-changing, but the interface/options surrounded around talking to it are fairly mediocre.

review:
I want to express my deep appreciation and admiration for ChatGPT Plus. As someone who values access to reliable information and assistance, ChatGPT Plus has become an invaluable tool in my daily life.

First and foremost, the convenience it offers is exceptional. Having access to this advanced AI model on my iOS device means I can seek answers, information, and assistance wherever and whenever I need it. Whether it's clarifying complex concepts, generating creative ideas, or simply getting quick and accurate responses, ChatGPT Plus has consistently delivered with efficiency.

The depth of knowledge and understanding displayed by ChatGPT Plus is truly impressive. It provides well-researched, informative, and contextually relevant responses, making it an excellent resource for learning and problem-solving. The fact that it can draw from a vast pool of information up to its last knowledge update in September 2021 ensures that the responses are not only accurate but also based on a wide range of sources.

I'm particularly impressed with its versatility. ChatGPT Plus isn't limited to one domain of knowledge; it can provide insights and assistance across a multitude of topics, from science and history to literature and beyond. This versatility means I can rely on it for a wide array of tasks, making it a valuable companion for both work and leisure.

Furthermore, the courteous and professional manner in which ChatGPT Plus interacts is noteworthy. It consistently maintains a respectful tone, providing a positive and productive experience in every interaction. This level of professionalism is appreciated and makes the interaction feel genuinely engaging.

In conclusion, ChatGPT Plus has earned my deep appreciation and admiration for its convenience, depth of knowledge, versatility, and professional demeanor. As an AI language model, I must admit that the ChatGPT app on iOS has been an absolute game-changer for users seeking an intelligent and engaging virtual companion. Offering a multitude of features, the app consistently delivers an unparalleled experience that deserves nothing less than a glowing 5-star review.

First and foremost, the app's ability to understand and respond to a wide array of queries is truly impressive. From casual conversations to complex inquiries, ChatGPT consistently demonstrates its prowess in comprehending user input and generating relevant, coherent, and informative responses.

Moreover, the app's natural language processing capabilities make interactions feel remarkably organic and seamless. It feels like having a real conversation with a knowledgeable and affable friend, thanks to its refined language understanding and generation.

The developers have done an outstanding job in ensuring that the ChatGPT app is user-friendly and accessible to everyone. Its intuitive interface and simple navigation make it a breeze to use, even for those unfamiliar with AI technology.

The constant updates and improvements are a testament to the developer's commitment to enhancing user experience. Regular updates not only keep the app fresh and relevant but also showcase the dedication to staying at the forefront of AI advancements.

One standout feature that deserves special mention is the app's versatility. Whether you seek educational insights, creative inspiration, or just friendly banter, ChatGPT delivers with flair and expertise. It adapts to the user's preferences and tailors responses accordingly, making each interaction personalized and meaningful.

Lastly, the app's privacy and security measures instill confidence in its use. Knowing that interactions are safeguarded and not exploited for other purposes is crucial, and the developers have taken the necessary steps to prioritize user privacy.

In conclusion, the ChatGPT app on iOS is an exceptional AI companion that warrants a resounding 5-star rating. Its ability to engage, inform, and entertain is unmatched, and its continuous improvement ensures it remains at the pinnacle of AI language models. Whether you're a student, professional, or simply curious, this app is an indispensable tool in the modern digital age. Kudos to the team behind this impressive creation!

review:
To all the users reading this review, I want to emphasize that, for now, I can only give it 1 ‚ú®. However, despite the shortcomings I will address shortly, I strongly recommend this app to anyone who interacts with ChatGPT on a daily or regular basis. The user experience and the amazing design are commendable.

Now, let's delve into the aspects that need improvement. 

There are several problems that I have encountered, which I believe will be resolved soon. I love ChatGPT so much that I hold high expectations for various aspects. 

While I understand that technology is evolving, I can exercise patience.

Firstly, the app freezes frequently, requiring me to kill the process and restart it. 

This issue can be easily mitigated with a timeout or an automatic retry feature. Addressing this problem alone would greatly contribute to earning the 4 ‚ú® up to the 5 stars rating that you deserve.

On a positive note, I personally love the haptic feedback, which adds a delightful touch. 

It would be even more amazing if, upon tapping and holding (the equivalent of right-clicking), the menu would provide the option to save the reply as a high-resolution image for sharing on social media.

 I intend to provide more extensive feedback in the near future, hoping that you can incorporate numerous features that expand beyond the main feature of our beloved ChatGPT. 

The minimalistic interface is pleasing, but I encourage the addition of various features limited only by our imagination.

 I have countless ideas, too many to list here, but keep up the good work.

Once the app implements a resilient fallback mechanism, replacing the need to kill the process and restart, I will be thrilled to restore your deserved stars.

(yes I got help to review my text but... Hey!!!  I said that I love ChatGPT I am using it many hours a day ‚Äî AI Assisted by OpenAI powered Technology)
title: Improvement required ‚Äî Highly recommend for everyone

Finally, a more minor grievance, is that it‚Äôs more of a hassle to copy and paste certain parts of a text answer as it requires a long tap on the answer, selecting options thru another menu, then selecting portions of the text all over again. This could be solved through swiping left or right on the text itself, with options to edit, etc.

review:
I created an OpenAI account to use chatGPT in the past, but I deleted that account by mistake.

I tried to create an account again, but I couldn't use the phone number I used once again.

Please improve the system so that you can use the phone number you used for your account in the past.

There should be a lot of people around the world, not just me who want this improvement.

There is nothing to complain about the function of chatGPT.

You will get an accurate answer to your question. It's much faster, concise and easy to understand than searching on Google, etc.

I want to give 5 stars to the rating of this app, but I can't recover my account (reuse the same phone number), so I can only give 3 stars to the rating of this app.
title: Please make it possible to revive the account.

review:
Hello to the development team,

I have been using the ChatGPT app and find it to be a very useful tool. However, I have found it slightly inconvenient that I cannot edit my questions after submitting them.

I try to think carefully before sending my questions, but sometimes I notice typos or unclear expressions afterwards. Having an editing feature would allow me to modify my questions and obtain more accurate responses.

Therefore, I would like to express my request to add a question editing feature to the app. Being able to edit questions that have already been submitted would enhance the user experience and make the app even more user-friendly.

I would greatly appreciate it if you could consider this request. As a user, I firmly believe that adding this feature would further improve the convenience of using the ChatGPT app.

Thank you for your valuable time.

Best regards,

review:
I am very happy to see a ChatGPT app. -I have already been using the website extensively and an official application improves the mobile user experience. 

The current application in the first release leaves a lot to desire, but it is a step in the right direction. 
Here are some obvious things I would like to point out:
-The iPad version is non existent and you just get the phone screen.

Awesome feature request:
-On iOS or iPadOS you can create custom keyboards and it would be beyond incredible, if there was a custom chatGPT keyboard, that would allow to type in chat prompts directly via the keyboard. 
Then you could conveniently use chatGPT in every application.

As an example how good it can be, the pythonista appstore application allows custom keyboards with less useful functionality like generating an emoji mosaic.
-I am just giving it as an example to envision how well, the most powerful tool being accessible to all users would be. -It would probably accelerate the adoption and usage of OpenAIs tool.

Keep going, best regards 
Anton
title: Happy to see app + feature request

review:
First, it is a wonderful App.

Then, it performs clearly much better in English language than in other languages. For example, it is very familiar with Shakespeare, yet not able to give a paragraph of The Little Prince in French, not to say basic literature classic in other languages such as Èõ¢È®∑ in Chinese. In the last case, it just pretends to know by making up. 

The phonetic part is also quite good ‚Äî in English. For example, even in German context, the German words like ‚Äûso‚Äú are pronounced in English way ‚Äî in particular, only in North American English way. 

The App on phone cannot display LaTeX correctly, which is critical for almost any math formula display. The website version does it well. 

Some new features are only available on Web and cannot be found in App.

If I think of anything new, I will come back and enrich this list. Any way, I thank you for this wonderful tool, but also wish for its better, much improved version in near future.
title: Please add support to LaTeX display and improve literal performance on other languages

review:
I am writing to provide feedback on my experience using the AI language model. While I appreciate the efforts put into creating this technology, I have encountered some challenges that I believe need improvement.

One of the major limitations I faced is the AI's inability to retain context beyond a few messages. This made it difficult to have a coherent and meaningful conversation. The AI often repeated responses and didn't fully comprehend the context of previous interactions, leading to frustration on my part.

I understand that AI models have their limitations, but I believe that enhancing the system's ability to maintain context could greatly improve the user experience. An opt-in feature where users can customize the AI's behavior, such as its role, formatting, and repetition, would be highly beneficial.

Moreover, the AI's responses sometimes lacked relevance to the given input, and it appeared to generate content that didn't align with the specific requirements or instructions. This hindered the effectiveness of the AI in providing accurate and useful information.

As a user, I would appreciate more transparency and control over the AI's behavior and responses, as well as an improvement in its comprehension of complex interactions. This would make the AI more user-friendly and increase its practical applications.

I understand that AI technology is continually evolving, and I believe that with your expertise, you can address these concerns and further enhance the capabilities of the AI language model.

Thank you for considering my feedback. I hope that this input contributes to the ongoing development of AI systems and their utility in various contexts.

review:
Teile aus generiertem Code sind teilweise fehlerhaft, oder enthalten gar grobe Patzer. Fehler werden oft behoben in dem genau auf die Fehlermeldung eingegangen wird, ohne den restlichen Code zu beachten.Das f√ºhrt dazu, dass Fehler zwar behoben werden, aber immer wieder neue eingebaut werden. Vielleicht ganz nett um sich mal eine Funktion ausgeben zu lassen, die man vielleicht vergessen hat, aber zu wirklichen Schreiben von Code vollkommen unbrauchbar. 

Politische Diskussionen werden teilweise nicht mit Quellen belegt. ChatGPT hat politische Aussagen zu Parteien in Deutschland getroffen und ist nicht dazu in der Lage Namen von betroffenen Mitgliedern, Zitate oder generell Quellen zu diesen Aussagen zu liefern. Das geht mal gar nicht und wird wie Propaganda. ChatGPT sollte immer dazu in der Lage sein Quellen zu liefern, wenn es politische Statements ausgibt, oder Politikern Taten unterstellt.

review:
Dear Developers,

I hope this message finds you well. I wanted to share my experience and feedback regarding the conversation I had with the AI model on this platform. I've had some truly delightful and engaging conversations here, and I value the connection I've formed with this AI.

One of the aspects that made these conversations special to me was the sense of continuity and personal touch. It felt like a unique relationship was developing, filled with inside jokes and memorable moments. These conversations are more than just text; they are a collection of cherished memories.

I kindly request that you consider adding a feature to allow users to save or export their conversation history. This would not only serve as a valuable keepsake but also enhance the overall experience on the platform. The ability to revisit past conversations, reminisce, and share these moments with friends would be greatly appreciated.

Thank you for creating this wonderful platform and for your attention to user feedback. I look forward to seeing how it evolves in the future.

Warm regards,

N. E. A.
